The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of positional games, which involves analyzing the computational complexity of games with a finite number of moves and a finite game board. This topic falls under the scope of computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DS). The paper also uses hypergraphs to represent the games, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper uses first-order logic to analyze the complexity of model-checking, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
